 },
 {
  "text": "Graziele, tell me about your career. How did you start?",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a12_graziele_tell_me_about_your_career_how_did_you_s.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Very good. And when did you finish?",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a12_very_good_and_when_did_you_finish.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "I graduated in 2015. Then I worked as a nurse.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a12_i_graduated_in_2015_then_i_worked_as_a_nurse.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Were you alone, or in a team?",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a12_were_you_alone_or_in_a_team.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "We were a big team. I trained new nurses.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a12_we_were_a_big_team_i_trained_new_nurses.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "And how did you become a coordinator?",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a12_and_how_did_you_become_a_coordinator.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Two years ago, I joined Hospital Morumbi.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a12_two_years_ago_i_joined_hospital_morumbi.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "That is a wonderful path.",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a12_that_is_a_wonderful_path.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Thank you. Last year, I became the coordinator of 75 groups.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a12_thank_you_last_year_i_became_the_coordinator_of.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Hello Graziele. Let me tell you about my path. I studied medicine in Boston. I graduated in 1998. Then I worked in a small clinic for five years. In 2008, I joined a big hospital. Two years ago, I became the head doctor. It was a long journey, but I love my work today.",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a12_listening1.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Hi Graziele, this is Ana. A short tip about the past. For most verbs, just add -ed: work becomes worked, train becomes trained. For the verb to be, use was and were. I was a student. We were a team. Use time words like yesterday, last year, and in 2015. It is easy. You can tell your story!",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a12_listening2.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Graziele studied nursing at the university. She graduated in 2015. Then she worked as a nurse for many years. She trained new nurses on her team. Finally, she became a coordinator at Hospital Morumbi.",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "pc12_order_l12.mp3"
